Comes with a ticking time bomb. [Left click] to toggle the timer on and off, but make sure you hop out before it explodes!
A huge truck with massive health and 5 passenger seats. The back 3 seats allow for a full 360 degree shooting range.
[Left Click] to fire 2 homing missiles that deal huge damage against vehicles and zombies.

[Left Click] to fire a deadly flamethrower. The Cybertruck is shatterproof.
Silent and deadly. The knife kills enemies in a single shot.
Kaboom! This deals huge damage if it explodes at your enemies feet.

Fires a missile that deals huge damage against vehicles and zombies.

An auto-shotgun with huge close range DPS. Charge up close and blast your enemies away!

Very effective at range, but you'll need to burst fire to control its recoil.
Accurate and great at range. It's silenced so nearby guards won't hear you fire it.

An extremely high damage superweapon that deals extra damage against zombies.

Hover here to view the skills menu.
click skills above to add them to the selected queue
You cannot queue skills unless you are playing in a Quickmatch.
There are two ways to resurrect - killing a living survivor, or finding the Genetic Heart.
Press (ENTER) to chat. Say 'wassup' to receive a bonus 20xp!
Each kill gives you +1 score and increases your gun's damage.
Stand on a gun and press (E). Your ammo is shown at the bottom right.
Enter a car by pressing (E). You can fire out the windows. Hold (Right Mouse) to use its boost.
Hold (ALT) and click 'Reset Skill Build' from the drop-down skills menu up the top of the screen.
Spend 2 skill points on 'Plasma Ball'. Right click skills to queue up future skill points.
Cast Plasma Ball with Right Click. The best way to find skill points is from supply drops.
This is the Outbreak game mode. To win you need to kill zombies, collect their souls and return them to the bomb.
After collecting souls you need to return them to the bomb. Follow the arrow on your screen to take your souls to the bomb. Hold (TAB) to see your score.
Buy the 'Synthetic Shop' chemical. When you carry this chemical, your ammo will last longer.
Place 'Synthetic Shop' with (CTRL). This create a buy zone. It also gives you cash over time.
Stand in your 'Synthetic Shop' and press (B) and buy ammo.
Pick up your chemical by standing in it and pressing (CTRL).
This is the Conquest game mode where you need to capture all of the Control Points in the map. You can do this extra fast with the 'Capturer' chemical. Buy a 'Capturer' chemical from your spawn zone.
Capture a point by holding (CTRL) and placing your Capturer on top of it. Hold (TAB) to see scores.
This is the Extraction game mode. Follow the white arrow on your screen to capture the enemy flag.
Follow the arrow and take the flag to the enemy flag near your spawn. Hold (TAB) to see your score.
This is the Checkpoint game mode. To win you need do laps with the Battery in a vehicle. Grab a car, then follow the white arrow on your screen to pick up the Battery.
Follow the white arrow on your screen to drive the battery through each of the checkpoints. Hold (TAB) to see your score.
Buy the 'Neutralizer' chemical and place it inside a chemical (yours or an enemies) to destroy it and earn cash (hold CTRL).
Press (F10) to finish this tutorial. This opens the How to Play Guide if you want to learn more.
Try to survive the round! This takes 3 minutes and gives +20 score.
Stand inside a buy zone (the yellow circles), and press (B) to buy ammo.
Press (SHIFT) to shift. Shifts are shown below your health bar.
When you get 60 points you gain extra damage. Then win one final round to win the game!
Select your knife with (3) and hold the mouse to charge it. Once you turn red you can kill in a single shot.
Find a civilian with a green text bubble above him and press (E).
Missions are shown above the minimap. Complete them to gain powerful bonuses (shown in green above your weapons).
Learn to play and earn bonus XP!
The player count, timer, and your score are shown here.
Your health, mana and shifts are shown down here.
Press 1, 2, 3 to select weapons, and middle mouse to throw grenades.
Press Right Mouse, C & F to cast skills. Hold ALT to buy skill points.
to toggle this guide on and off.

The meaning of life, the universe and everything you need to know about Geneshift can be found in this guide; so toggle this back on when you're ready to play like a pro. Until then you can press ENTER to chat with the server and ask questions. Have fun!

EARN A LITTLE EXTRA ON THE SIDE..
What do I have to do?
Follow the arrow on your screen to reach the next checkpoint. Try to earn combo kills to gain extra cash.
What if I miss some text?
Press (ENTER) to bring up the chat log. The green lines have important tips. Also when playing singleplayer you can hold (ALT) to pause the game and read the text at your own pace.
Stay out of combat for a few seconds to trigger auto-heal. Use vehicles for protection while looting. Unlock healing skills with (ALT). Buy expensive weapons to deal extra damage.
You gain +1 point per kill, and +20 points if you're the last man standing. When you reach enough points you'll gain extra damage. The game will then end when you win your next round.
Avoid the circle of death and try to stay alive. Survival is key! If you become a zombie use this time to loot for cash. Or try resurrect with the Genetic Heart or by killing a survivor.

When you view the skills page through the main menu you're looking at your permanent skill build. This build is only used in permanent multiplayer servers and persists between rounds. This build is not used in quickmatches or the campaign.
Here you can host multiplayer modes and play against bots. To play against humans it's usually better to join an official server.
You can improve your FPS by updating your graphics drivers. For now, would you like Geneshift to optimise your graphics settings?
No. The human eye can only see 30 FPS.
